<p style="margin:0 0 22px;font-size:18px;line-height:1.6;color:#1a1a1a">You feel it before you're even out of bed. The hands that won't quite close. The knee that needs a minute before it'll take your weight.</p>
<p style="margin:0 0 22px;font-size:18px;line-height:1.6;color:#1a1a1a">You've tried to get ahead of it. The diclofenac gel. Biofreeze. Tiger Balm. Cream after cream. <strong>Each one cooled your skin for twenty minutes.</strong><br><strong>Then the stiffness came back exactly like before.</strong></p>
<p style="margin:0 0 22px;font-size:18px;line-height:1.6;color:#1a1a1a">And slowly, you stopped doing things. Opening a jar without calling for help. Buttoning a shirt without your fingers fighting you. Getting down on the floor with the grandkids, and back up again.</p>
<p style="margin:0;font-size:18px;line-height:1.6;color:#1a1a1a">Here's the thing: it was never you getting old, and it was never you giving up. Knuckles, knees, hips, hands, every one of them failed for the same reason. <strong>And once you see what it is, you can't unsee it.</strong></p>
